08/02/2004
MUNICH, Germany -- Albanian Defence Minister Pandeli Majko met with Croatian and Macedonian counterparts Berislav Roncevic and Vlado Buckovski on Saturday (7 February), on the sidelines of the 40th Conference on Security Policy in Munich. 
The three countries comprise the Adriatic Charter, and the three ministers discussed intensifying co-operation on the expert level within that charter. 
They also agreed to meet more often.
Majko also met separately with US Defence Secretary Donald Rumsfeld and German Defence Minister Peter Struck. 
They discussed bilateral co-operation in the field of military ties and defence strategies as well as steps Albania must take to move closer to NATO and contribute further to the international fight against terrorism. 
(ATA, HINA, MIA - 07/02/04)
